  <static seed="8" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring71.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{64t^{2}-32t+56}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>8\mathopen{}\left(8t^{2}-4t+7\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>8</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{64t^{2}-32t+56}={8\mathopen{}\left(8t^{2}-4t+7\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
